it's must, I suppose just childlike I don't know, I got on very well with my dad and when my dad died - he died in 1913, after a rather long illness, he was ill about three or four months - seemed a long time to us. I remember coming home from the office 
m
eeting a little girl from next door and she said your father's very - I think your father's very ill because the doctor and the priest has been. Of course priest, he was very friendly with one of the clergy and he was with him most of the day he came to s
