e loaded those up, we had each section, there was A, B, C, d. There were four sections and each had two ammunition wagons. So that was four twos - four twos are eight - four guns, twelve - we had about sixty G.S. Wagons - general service wagons - and all 
t
his had to be loaded up and all the stores and everything else and on the way we - we joined up the horses and everything else - we joined up onto the train and I remember we went down - during the night. We left - at eleven o'clock at night. About eight 
