 all the horses and then fed them - water and feed them that's first thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6837232\charrsid4933843 
That was one thing about animals - you were not allowed to have any meal yourself until all the horses were attended to you see, so water and fed them and then the bugler went in w
hen we got in - of course it was kind of - very interesting for the people waiting for the trains watching the soldiers doing their bit. We did - we were really a very good battery and the whole length of the train of course were horses, guns and every' t
hing. We - we moved in then to Borden which was then about a couple of miles from Aldershot - we were there three weeks getting our final equipment and everything else before we went overseas. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
