Well there was always that - my brother was always - kind of - I'm the oldest one and mother used to look up to him to do - to see to everything. And you always felt that he was - taking over but - mind you I suppose j
ust as someone had to look after the home and that. But - prior to - I also had interests outside - I was a member of the - when I came home from the war I still went back to church to - to help and one of the gentlemen asked me if I would join the St Vin
cent Paul Society. That was the society where you used to go out and - meet old people and people -
